The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Sept. 9: The RBI today said bank finance to developers of infrastructure facilities in SEZs would be considered as infrastructure lending against its 2006 ruling that classified these as commercial real estate (CRE) exposures. Banks can finance cost of land development, which will be classified as CRE as the source of repayment will be lease rentals, according to the RBIs guidelines on the definition of CRE exposures.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 9: Anil Ambanis RNRL today told the Supreme Court that the governments approval was not required for the sale of gas by RIL to it and alleged that the Mukesh Ambani-led company had wrongfully and mischievously sought to pass this off as a condition.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 9: Indias position in terms of ease of doing business globally has slipped one place to 133rd this year, according to the International Finance Corporations Doing Business 2010 survey.                             
	 Calcutta, Sept. 9: The Bengal government today recommended a 10 per cent bonus for the 2.5 lakh jute mill workers in the state. September 15 is the deadline for the payment.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 9: Workers at the countrys major ports have called off their indefinite strike from September 15 after they reached a consensus with the government on wage revision.                                                                                                                           
